00:01:31,070 --> 00:01:34,979
[The Lost National Treasure]

2
00:01:35,039 --> 00:01:37,729
[Episode 24]

3
00:01:39,310 --> 00:01:42,770
Throughout his life, Confucius
narrated but did not compose.

4
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:46,479
At your age, you're already writing
books and establishing theories.

5
00:01:46,479 --> 00:01:47,810
I need to learn from you.

6
00:01:47,950 --> 00:01:48,950
I'm flattered.

7
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,840
There's nothing
you're afraid of me hearing, right?

8
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,710
What could I possibly
have that I'm afraid of you hearing?

9
00:01:53,710 --> 00:01:55,020
I write books and give lectures,

10
00:01:55,020 --> 00:01:56,020
it's not illegal.

11
00:01:56,070 --> 00:01:56,870
That's right.

12
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,400
Well.

13
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,760
Much of what you say
is too profound for me.

14
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,020
I don't understand it.

15
00:02:04,070 --> 00:02:04,600
However,

16
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,170
I heard a few sentences,

17
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:11,150
are you trying
to whitewash those tomb raiders?

18
00:02:11,340 --> 00:02:12,540
That can't be, right?

19
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:14,720
You can't say such things carelessly.

20
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,660
That's too big an accusation.

21
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,140
Let's just say
it's a difference in personal views.

22
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,400
Oh, it's academic.

23
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:25,430
I'm just a simple man,
I don't understand these things.

24
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:27,710
Anyway, it's about cultural relics, right?

25
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:29,840
I mean, cultural relics are like life.

26
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,150
Real artifacts can't be faked,

27
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:34,910
and fake ones can't become real.

28
00:02:34,910 --> 00:02:37,710
As for people,
you should walk the righteous path.

29
00:02:37,730 --> 00:02:39,790
If you take crooked ways and detours,

30
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:40,680
in the end,

31
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:44,620
good and evil
will eventually be rewarded accordingly.

32
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:45,220
Am I right?

33
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:46,360
You're right.

34
00:02:47,630 --> 00:02:48,890
There's an old saying,

35
00:02:49,260 --> 00:02:50,280
if a person doesn't touch the ground,

36
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,079
their feet naturally won't get muddy.

37
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,480
Right.

38
00:02:52,970 --> 00:02:53,630
Captain Qi,

39
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:55,680
come visit my little shop someday.

40
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:56,970
You know where it is.

41
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,820
You're welcome anytime.

42
00:02:58,820 --> 00:03:00,620
I'll continue to learn from you.

43
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:02,060
Well, I'll be going now.

44
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:03,260
Goodbye, Captain Qi.

45
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:08,400
How about giving me a copy of that book?

46
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,060
No problem.

47
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:10,800
Come to the store
to pick it up when you're free.

48
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,200
It's all been delivered?

49
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,290
Sold out today.

50
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:15,930
There's nothing left.

51
00:03:16,370 --> 00:03:17,170
See you later.

52
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:23,920
Captain Yang.

53
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:26,450
Captain Qi, come here.

54
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:30,190
Mu Jianhui has published a book.

55
00:03:30,870 --> 00:03:31,200
What?

56
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,090
What do you think he's up to?

57
00:03:38,370 --> 00:03:40,900
"Appreciation of Black Pottery Figurines."

58
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:46,730
After the Lv Family Tomb incident,

59
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,710
we've been keeping an eye on him.

60
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:50,440
There haven't been any issues.

61
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,310
His brother-in-law
opened a construction company.

62
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:56,240
It seems like
they're running a legitimate business.

63
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:58,470
We're also watching his Nameless Pavilion.

64
00:03:58,470 --> 00:04:00,270
It just sells some handicrafts.

65
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:02,630
It doesn't have
any connections to the underworld.

66
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:03,520
Overall,

67
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,480
his business seems very clean.

68
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:07,630
Do you know

69
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,770
how many copies he printed?

70
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:11,120
How many?

71
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,200
Ten thousand copies?

72
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:14,310
A hundred thousand.

73
00:04:14,310 --> 00:04:14,640
What?

74
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,660
He paid for it himself.

75
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,510
It cost him one or two million.

76
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,829
He's loaded.

77
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:23,430
That's an astronomical figure.

78
00:04:26,870 --> 00:04:29,600
It seems his way
of making money is questionable.

79
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,720
We just haven't figured it out yet.

80
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:36,390
Tell me,

81
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:39,870
investing one or two million like that,

82
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,510
he must be expecting
some kind of response.

83
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:45,710
What kind of response is he looking for?

84
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:50,480
He must be

85
00:04:51,390 --> 00:04:52,850
wanting to become famous.

86
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,870
After dealing with him for so long,

87
00:04:57,830 --> 00:04:59,750
what kind of person do you think he is?

88
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:00,830
Well, Mu Jianhui

89
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:02,420
doesn't drink,

90
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:03,810
doesn't smoke,

91
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,070
doesn't visit prostitutes or gamble,

92
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,730
he's very self-disciplined.

93
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:09,510
I think

94
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:12,800
compared to the people
from the underworld we've dealt with,

95
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:13,560
he's completely different.

96
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,220
He's extremely,
extremely self-disciplined.

97
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,860
He doesn't even care about money,

98
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,600
doesn't care about houses,

99
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,000
doesn't care about cars.

100
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,270
He just loves his wife

101
00:05:23,630 --> 00:05:24,490
and his family.

102
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,630
It's not right to say
he has no material desires though.

103
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:31,950
At the very least,

104
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,430
you see,

105
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:34,390
that guy,

106
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,100
he loves antiques.

107
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:37,860
But his love for antiques

108
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:39,630
is open and aboveboard.

109
00:05:40,630 --> 00:05:43,159
And he loves them
with great sophistication.

110
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:45,670
His historical knowledge is very rich.

111
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:47,250
He's a scholar,

112
00:05:47,870 --> 00:05:48,270
right?

113
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:52,650
Dacang,

114
00:05:54,430 --> 00:05:55,310
I feel

115
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,920
you're getting close
to figuring out Mu Jianhui.

116
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,250
What have I figured out?

117
00:05:59,630 --> 00:06:01,270
He's a great person.

118
00:06:01,680 --> 00:06:03,280
I can't figure out anything.

119
00:06:15,970 --> 00:06:16,420
Kun.

120
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,480
Kun.

121
00:06:19,090 --> 00:06:20,550
We're here. Almost there.

122
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,200
So many cars coming.

123
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:37,850
Must be visiting
relatives for the New Year.

124
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:42,370
The New Year's over.
Where are these relatives coming from?

125
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:54,320
No one is allowed in.

126
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,310
Where are you all from?
What are you doing here?

127
00:06:57,310 --> 00:06:57,840
No entry.

128
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:01,030
Nobody is allowed in.

129
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,510
No entry, I said no entry!

130
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,870
Why won't you let us in?

131
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:07,190
I said no entry. Step back!

132
00:07:07,490 --> 00:07:08,070
Back off!

133
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,600
Step back!

134
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:10,760
Move back!

135
00:07:11,430 --> 00:07:13,510
Back off, back off! What are you doing?

136
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:14,510
Calm down, let's talk this through.

137
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:15,630
What's going on? What's the situation?

138
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:16,680
They're saying that...

139
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,430
Our village has some emperor or something.

140
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:20,800
Don't know where
they heard it from. So many cars here.

141
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,160
I can't even write
down all the license plates.

142
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,070
What emperor?

143
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,040
They want to enter the village to see it.

144
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,970
No one can enter.

145
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:26,630
Why can't we go in?

146
00:07:26,630 --> 00:07:27,950
Wait, bro.

147
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:28,920
They're saying there's an emperor.

148
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,390
Where did you hear
that there's an emperor in this village?

149
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,870
It's all over the internet.

150
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:34,560
They're saying
Yin Village has an emperor's tomb.

151
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,800
How come you're
not letting people in to see it?

152
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,800
It's not true. They're fooling you.

153
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,080
No, nobody is allowed in.

154
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,240
Uncle Shoucun, you stay here and guard.

155
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:43,920
I'll go back and check.

156
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,920
Call me if anything happens.

157
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,680
Don't get into any fights, you hear me?

158
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:47,010
Okay.

159
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,130
No entry, no entry!

160
00:07:52,050 --> 00:07:53,310
The dogs will bite you!

161
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:57,360
We heard the archaeological team
made a major discovery.

162
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,270
Can you give us
some details about the situation?

163
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,000
Tell us something!

164
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,680
Can you say something about it?

165
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:00,630
Please answer our questions.

166
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:01,600
Alright, alright, listen to me.

167
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,460
It's like this.

168
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,000
If there's any news,

169
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,870
we will immediately

170
00:08:05,870 --> 00:08:07,270
announce it to everyone

171
00:08:07,270 --> 00:08:08,300
through official media channels.

172
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:09,400
Aright? Thank you.

173
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:09,800
Let me through.

174
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,950
There are rumors online that a new large tomb
has been discovered in Yin Village.

175
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:13,480
What's the current
situation with the tomb?

176
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,810
Can you tell us about it?

177
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:16,190
Let me through.

178
00:08:17,270 --> 00:08:19,040
Everyone is very
concerned about this issue.

179
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,070
What exactly is the situation now?

180
00:08:20,070 --> 00:08:20,680
Can you tell us about it?

181
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:21,160
Please answer.

182
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,160
Please answer our questions.

183
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,960
Come on, everyone, listen to me.

184
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:25,660
Everyone, listen to me.

185
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,190
-If there are any discoveries...
-Hurry.

186
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:28,430
We will definitely announce them

187
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:31,760
through the official channels
of the archaeological team.

188
00:08:34,419 --> 00:08:35,220
What's wrong?

189
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,770
What's going on?

190
00:08:37,630 --> 00:08:38,480
This...

191
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,080
These people have gone crazy.

192
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:42,030
What's been going on these past few days?

193
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,090
What's happening?

194
00:08:43,270 --> 00:08:44,480
All these people suddenly showed up.

195
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,200
I'm worried bad people
might sneak in during the chaos.

196
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,910
Uncle Shoucun
is guarding at the village entrance.

197
00:08:47,910 --> 00:08:49,630
Mr. Fang, what's really going on here?

198
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:50,550
Looking at the situation now,

199
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:51,600
I guess it's about the Yin Village matter

200
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:52,670
that the outside world
has found out about.

201
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:54,270
How could the outside world know?

202
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:55,510
We few certainly didn't say anything.

203
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:55,870
That's right.

204
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,510
Who knows?

205
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:57,790
Let's not worry about
how the outside world found out for now.

206
00:08:57,790 --> 00:08:59,270
We should report this
to the station first.

207
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:00,200
Director Zhang,

208
00:09:00,270 --> 00:09:01,080
You and Fang Kun

209
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:03,080
return to the station immediately.

210
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,580
Alright, understood.

211
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,270
What's up?

212
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,640
Director Zhang wants us
to go back to the station now.

213
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:12,400
[A grave emerged in Yin Village. It's hard to tell if it's true or not.]

214
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:16,080
Director Zhang.

215
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:18,870
Why did you call us back so urgently?

216
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:24,670
See for yourself.

217
00:09:47,390 --> 00:09:49,390
How did this become the talk of the town?

218
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:50,790
You have the nerve to ask?

219
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,270
Did you attend some kind of

220
00:09:52,270 --> 00:09:53,150
book launch?

221
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:55,790
There was someone named Mu

222
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:57,720
who talked about the Yin Village tomb.

223
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,580
There's even a video of it online.

224
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,060
That Mu person,

225
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,510
I had no idea who he was.

226
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,910
If I had known who that person was,

227
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:06,550
I definitely wouldn't have gone.

228
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:07,720
My friend told me

229
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,840
that person was some kind of scholar.

230
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:10,900
I believed it. I...

231
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:15,370
My fault.

232
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:19,010
I shouldn't have
attended that darn lecture.

233
00:10:20,790 --> 00:10:22,850
Don't take all the blame on yourself.

234
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:26,550
It's clear that word
has already spread in our circles.

235
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:28,750
Someone must have leaked the information.

236
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:30,550
The power of new media these days

237
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,000
is really something.

238
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,330
Even the smallest thing

239
00:10:33,630 --> 00:10:35,290
spreads faster than a rocket.

240
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,610
In our line of work,

241
00:10:38,790 --> 00:10:41,390
although it's not
as dangerous as Qi Dacang's,

242
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,300
you have to realize

243
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,550
how many eyes
are watching you from behind,

244
00:10:46,550 --> 00:10:48,410
trying to drag you down, you know?

245
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:51,120
So now, this situation,

246
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:53,670
what should we do?

247
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,500
What do you think we should do?

248
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:59,150
How about I go back to Yin Village first?

249
00:10:59,150 --> 00:11:00,390
A lot of outsiders have come.

250
00:11:00,390 --> 00:11:01,120
I'm worried.

251
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,600
